         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">10/9/81. ¶  ¶ With much pleasure do I send to you, dear Mr Bailey, on the request of our friend, the Rev. B. Scortechini, the byefollowing Certificate for his Candidature of the L.S., which doubtless ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">81.09.10a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Frederick Bailey</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">ML MSS B202, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">10/9/81.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With much pleasure do I send to you, dear Mr Bailey, on the request of our friend, the Rev. B. Scortechini, the byefollowing Certificate for his Candidature of the L.S., which doubtless you &amp; the Rev. Tenison-Wood will also sign.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Scortechini was proposed for the Linnean Society of London on 1 December 1881 by M, Bailey and L. A. Bernays, and was elected on 19 January <seg style="color: #000000; ">1882 (see certificate, in this edition as 81-09-00b).</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> I am glad that so worthy a worker in the fields of religion &amp; natural science will join the L.S., which now soon will celebrate its centenary Jubilee.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The Linnean Society celebrated its centenary in 1888.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have nothing of prominent interest to communicate concerning QL.,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Qld.</p>
               </note> in which you are specially interested, but shall have an other number of the Fragmenta out by December.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B81.13.02?</p>
               </note> The meliaceous tree, concerning which I wrote to you as occurring on the Wild River<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Qld. M's letter not found.</p>
               </note> is perhaps as a sub-genus to be placed into Dysoxylon, but that I can only determine when I get ripe fruit. It is very near a New Guinea <name key="Dysoxylon%20caulostachyum">Dysoxylon caulostachyum</name>
               <note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">caulostachyum <seg style="font-style: italic; ">interlined</seg>.</p>
               </note> described lately, but the calyx is completely closed &amp; eggshaped before the flower expands. This is quite unique in Meliaceae, as you may know, but the flowers from the stem occur also in Dys. oppositifolium of QL., and in D. spectabile from N. Zealand and some Java &amp; Papuan species.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Mr Scortechini says that Dr Bancroft &amp; Mr Bernays might sign the application paper, as the Rev T. Woods will be back only about Christmas.<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Woods spent part of 1881 in north Qld.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I sent a proof of the new number of Fragm<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B81.08.03?</p>
               </note> to Scortechini, and hope the lot of copies will be out this week.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Dysoxylon%20caulostachyum">Dysoxylon caulostachyum</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Dysoxylon%20oppositifolium">Dysoxylon oppositifolium</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Dysoxylon%20spectabile">Dysoxylon spectabile</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
